         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <ab>
            <lg>
               <l> As I saw the manuscript, thus I copied it, whether nonsensical or meaningful. No
                  fault is mine. O bird-like mind, once you have left Śiva who is like a
                  wish-fulfilling tree (read °kalpa° for °talpa°), whose roots are bliss, its
                  sprouts are the qualities, its branches are the truth, its flowers and fruits are
                  the Vedānta, its sap is liberation, what (read kim for kid) will you do in the
                  withered bush of saṃsāra?</l>
            </lg>
         Year called Vikāri, month of Phālguna, 19th day, Vayalakkāvūr Ekāmbraṃ copied with
               his own hand. The text (°grandhaṃ) called Śivagītā is completed. 
            </ab>
